cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is about a new tool for training neural network language models, which is a topic that falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Theano, a popular deep learning library, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of GPUs and parallelization, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
